  "sourceCode": "Employer Portal",
  "title": "QA/QC Assistant",
  "description": "<p><u><strong>Job Responsibilities:</strong></u><br />• Carry out daily hygiene inspection to ensure stringent reinforcement of food hygiene safety in practice.<br />• Perform routine quality checks on raw materials, in-process products and finished goods.<br />• Check and maintain cleaning & sanitation records, pests control records and production logs. <br />• Ensure microbiological laboratory carried out are according to company and government's regulatory standards.<br />• Assist in customers' feedback, product rejections and discuss with the relevant departments on the corrective & preventive actions required.<br />• Support preparation for SFA inspections, audits and internal audits.<br />• Assist with maintaining quality documentation, ensuring all records are up-to-date and accurate.<br />• Work closely with production staffs to foster a culture of quality and continuous improvement.<br />• Perform any other ad-hoc duties as assigned by the Manager. <br /><br /><u><strong>Job Requirements:</strong></u><br />• <strong>Singaporeans Only</strong><br />• Applicant must possess at least Diploma/ Advanced Diploma/ Graduate Diploma/ Bachelors' Degree in Food Science & Technology. <br />• At least 1 year of QA/QC experience in food manufacturing, food processing or central kitchen environment.<br />• Familiar with SFA regulation and documentation required.<br />• Detail-oriented, hands-on and able to follow instructions.<br />• Ability to work in a fast-paced environment and handle multiple tasks.<br />• Team-player with good communication skills. </p>",
